<br>
All I can tell you about is the following AA skills that are outside defensive ones but ADD a HUGE amount of aggro.<br>
<br>
Combat Fury 3<br>
Flurry 3<br>
Ferocity 2<br>
Fury of the Ages 3<br>
Punishing Blade 3<br>
Raging Flurry 2<br>
TM 2<br>
<br>
Using mainly a 2h Twisted Steel Bastard Sword and a 2h Primal War Lance.  I have out aggroed level wizards, rogues, rangers etc. You name it..I out aggroed it.  Even when someone had 275aa backing them.<br>
<br>
Okay now someone is going to say &quot; extra damage does not improve aggro&quot;.  LOL..it sure does.  With the above skills and being level 65 also I do 120 dps on a low to 150 dps on a high which both were around 70% speed.  I rarely lose aggro when in a group.<br>
<br>
When I upgraded just to Punishing Blade 3 I saw an increase of around 20% in damage done and the following happened.<br>
My minimum hit went from 1 to 18.<br>
My maximum hit went from 587 to 735.<br>
My average hit went from 129 to 198.<br>
<br>
Once upon a time I was in a uber guild and back then I was actually told to put away my 2h weapons since I was always stealing aggro from the MT who was tanking a major named mob.  The MT was decked out in over 100 defensive AA skills but lacked any offensive AA skills whereas I was balanced more towards offensive AA back then than defensive.<br>
<br>
So I would say get those offensive AA skills up as they do help a lot to keep aggro against any mob but also make sure if you want that much aggro you have the defensive skills to survive all the attention or you will fall like a &quot;paper tank in the wind&quot;.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps but remember that each of us have to choose our own paths to go by.  Choose whatever AA skills you are comfortable not what someone thinks you should have.<br>
<br>
PS...when I finish raging flurry 3 and tm 3 and ferocity 3 I plan to go back to TOVN and kick those stupid flying flurry type mobs that use to kick my butt. Ahhh...revenge is soooooo sweet<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
